import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='y', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['y'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'mean={data["y"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.axvline(data['y'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'median={data["y"].median():.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of y?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

    plt.title('What is the correlation between x and y?', wrap=True)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['diff'])
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='diff', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['diff'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['diff'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(x=data['diff'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['diff'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of diff?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='diff', data=data, ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('How does diff vary over time?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Diff')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
